@startuml MyAIStorybook Use Cases
' Use Case Diagram for MyAIStorybook - Based on Scope Document
' Shows use cases for the actual project scope

left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

' Define actors
actor "User\n(Parent/Educator/Child)" as User

' Define system boundary
rectangle "MyAIStorybook System" {
  
  ' Core Story Generation Use Cases
  usecase "UC1: Generate Story\nfrom Text Prompt" as UC1
  usecase "UC2: Generate Story\nfrom Voice Input" as UC2
  usecase "UC3: Interactive\nStory Chat" as UC3
  
  ' Media Generation Use Cases
  usecase "UC4: Generate\nStory Images" as UC4
  usecase "UC5: Generate\nStory Audio" as UC5
  usecase "UC6: Character\nConsistency" as UC6
  
  ' Export Use Cases
  usecase "UC7: Export Story\nto PDF" as UC7
  usecase "UC8: Export Story\nto Audio Book" as UC8
  
  ' User Experience Use Cases
  usecase "UC9: Toggle\nTheme" as UC9
  usecase "UC10: Customize\nUser Preferences" as UC10
  
  ' Internal sub-processes
  usecase "Validate Input" as UC1a
  usecase "Process Voice" as UC2a
  usecase "Generate Text" as UC1b
  usecase "Generate Images" as UC4a
  usecase "Generate Audio" as UC5a
  usecase "Quality Review" as UC1c
  usecase "Display Story" as UC1d
}

' User associations
User --> UC1
User --> UC2
User --> UC3
User --> UC4
User --> UC5
User --> UC6
User --> UC7
User --> UC8
User --> UC9
User --> UC10

' Include relationships
UC1 .> UC1a : <<include>>
UC1 .> UC1b : <<include>>
UC1 .> UC1c : <<include>>
UC1 .> UC1d : <<include>>

UC2 .> UC2a : <<include>>
UC2 .> UC1b : <<include>>
UC2 .> UC1c : <<include>>
UC2 .> UC1d : <<include>>

UC4 .> UC4a : <<include>>
UC5 .> UC5a : <<include>>

' Extend relationships
UC1 <.. UC4 : <<extend>>\n(optional)
UC1 <.. UC5 : <<extend>>\n(optional)
UC1 <.. UC6 : <<extend>>\n(optional)

UC2 <.. UC4 : <<extend>>\n(optional)
UC2 <.. UC5 : <<extend>>\n(optional)

UC3 <.. UC5 : <<extend>>\n(optional)

' Notes for major use cases
note right of UC1
  **Primary Use Case - Text Input**
  
  Preconditions:
  - System running
  - Valid text prompt entered
  
  Main Flow:
  1. User enters story prompt
  2. User selects generation options
  3. User clicks "Generate Story"
  4. System processes through agents
  5. System displays story with media
  
  Postconditions:
  - Story displayed with navigation
  - PDF created automatically
  - Images generated (if enabled)
  - Audio generated (if enabled)
end note

note right of UC2
  **Voice Input Mode**
  
  Preconditions:
  - Microphone access granted
  - Voice input detected
  
  Main Flow:
  1. User speaks story prompt
  2. System transcribes speech
  3. System processes as text prompt
  4. System generates story
  5. System provides audio feedback
  
  Postconditions:
  - Story generated from voice
  - Audio narration available
end note

note right of UC3
  **Interactive Chat Mode**
  
  Preconditions:
  - Chat mode enabled
  - User preferences set
  
  Main Flow:
  1. User starts conversation
  2. System responds contextually
  3. User can modify story elements
  4. System adapts to preferences
  5. User can generate final story
  
  Postconditions:
  - Interactive story experience
  - Personalized content
end note

note right of UC4
  **Image Generation with Character Consistency**
  
  Features:
  - IP-Adapter integration
  - Character consistency across scenes
  - High-resolution output
  - Scene composition
  - Artistic style options
end note

note right of UC5
  **Audio Generation**
  
  Features:
  - Coqui TTS synthesis
  - Voice style selection
  - Page-by-page narration
  - Accessibility support
end note

note bottom of User
  **User Demographics:**
  - Parents (40%)
  - Educators (30%)
  - Children (20%)
  - Content Creators (10%)
  
  **Usage Patterns:**
  - Home use (60%)
  - Educational (30%)
  - Professional (10%)
end note

@enduml

